   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Building NARX models using general estimators\n",
    "\n",
    "Example created by Wilson Rocha Lacerda Junior"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this example we will create NARX models using different estimator like GrandientBoostingRegressior, Bayesian Regression, Automatic Relevance Determination (ARD) Regression and Catboost"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pip install sysidentpy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "10-14 20:29:33 - INFO - Note: NumExpr detected 12 cores but \"NUMEXPR_MAX_THREADS\" not set, so enforcing safe limit of 8.\n",
      "10-14 20:29:33 - INFO - NumExpr defaulting to 8 threads.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from sysidentpy.metrics import mean_squared_error\n",
    "from sysidentpy.utils.generate_data import get_siso_data\n",
    "from sysidentpy.general_estimators import NARX\n",
    "from sklearn.linear_model import BayesianRidge, ARDRegression\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingRegressor\n",
    "from catboost import CatBoostRegressor"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# simulated dataset\n",
    "x_train, x_valid, y_train, y_valid = get_siso_data(n=10000,\n",
    "                                                   colored_noise=False,\n",
    "                                                   sigma=0.01,\n",
    "                                                   train_percentage=80)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Importance of the NARX architecture\n",
    "\n",
    "To get an idea of the importance of the NARX architecture, lets take a look in the performance of the models without the NARX configuration."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "catboost = CatBoostRegressor(iterations=300,\n",
    "                             learning_rate=0.1,\n",
    "                             depth=6)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "gb = GradientBoostingRegressor(loss='quantile', alpha=0.90,\n",
    "                                n_estimators=250, max_depth=10,\n",
    "                                learning_rate=.1, min_samples_leaf=9,\n",
    "                                min_samples_split=9)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_results(yvalid, yhat):\n",
    "    _, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 8))\n",
    "    ax.plot(y_valid[:200], label='Data', marker='o')\n",
    "    ax.plot(yhat[:200], label='Prediction', marker='*')\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel(\"$n$\", fontsize=18)\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel(\"$y[n]$\", fontsize=18)\n",
    "    ax.grid()\n",
    "    ax.legend(fontsize=18)\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1008x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "catboost.fit(x_train, y_train, verbose=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_results(y_valid, catboost.predict(x_valid))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "C:\\Users\\wilso\\miniconda3\\envs\\rd\\lib\\site-packages\\sklearn\\utils\\validation.py:63: DataConversionWarning: A column-vector y was passed when a 1d array was expected. Please change the shape of y to (n_samples, ), for example using ravel().\n",
      "  return f(*args, **kwargs)\n"
     ]

    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",

       "<Figure size 1008x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]

     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "gb.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "\n",
    "plot_results(y_valid, gb.predict(x_valid))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Introducing the NARX configuration using SysIdentPy\n",
    "\n",
    "As you can see, you just need to pass the base estimator you want to the NARX class from SysIdentPy do build the NARX model! You can choose the lags of the input and output variables to build the regressor matrix.\n",
    "\n",
    " We keep the fit/predict method to make the process straightforward."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### NARX with Catboost"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "10-14 20:29:57 - INFO - Training the model\n",
      "10-14 20:29:57 - INFO - Creating the regressor matrix\n",
      "10-14 20:29:57 - INFO - The regressor matrix have 5 features\n"
     ]
    },
    {

     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

    {

      "image/png": "",

      ]

     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"

   ],
   "source": [
    "from sysidentpy.general_estimators import NARX\n",
    "\n",
    "catboost_narx = NARX(base_estimator=CatBoostRegressor(iterations=300,\n",
    "                                                      learning_rate=0.1,\n",
    "                                                      depth=6),\n",
    "                     xlag=2,\n",
    "                     ylag=2,\n",
    "                     fit_params={'verbose': False}\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "catboost_narx.fit(x_train, y_train)\n",
    "yhat = catboost_narx.predict(x_valid, y_valid)\n",
    "print(mean_squared_error(y_valid, yhat))\n",
    "\n",
    "ee, ex, extras, lam = catboost_narx.residuals(x_valid, y_valid, yhat)\n",
    "catboost_narx.plot_result(y_valid, yhat, ee, ex, n=200)"
   ]
  },
